df-prod
blocks.content: Define the product of a series with an index set of integers ` A ` . This definition takes most of the aspects of ~ df-sum and adapts them for multiplication instead of addition. However, we insist that in the infinite case, there is a nonzero tail of the sequence. This ensures that the convergence criteria match those of infinite sums. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 4-Dec-2017.)

blocks.name: nfcprod
blocks.content: Bound-variable hypothesis builder for product: if ` x ` is (effectively) not free in ` A ` and ` B ` , it is not free in ` prod_ k e. A B ` . (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 1-Dec-2017.)

  nfcv(s0, c2)
}

  adantl(wa(w0, wcel(cv(hs0), cfv(cuz, c2))), wcel(cv(hs1), cc), wceq(co(cv(hs1), cmul, nat1), cv(hs1)))

  syl2anc(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), cfv(cuz, c0))), wceq(cfv(c1, cv(s0)), cif(c4, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c3))), wcel(cv(s0), cz), wcel(cif(c4, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c3)), cc))
  adantl(w0, wcel(cv(s0), cfv(cuz, c0)), wcel(cv(s0), cz))
  eluzelz(cv(s0), c0)
  pm2.61d1(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), cfv(cuz, c0))), wcel(cif(c4, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c3)), cc), wcel(cv(s0), c3))
  ex(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), cfv(cuz, c0))), wcel(cv(s0), c3), wcel(cif(c4, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c3)), cc))
  eqeltrd(cif(c4, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c3)), cc, c4, wa(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), cfv(cuz, c0))), wcel(cv(s0), c3)))
  adantl(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s0), cfv(cuz, c0))), wcel(cv(s0), c3), wceq(cif(c4, nat1, wcel(cv(s0), c3)), c4))

blocks.name: prodmo
blocks.content: A product has at most one limit. (Contributed by Scott Fenton, 4-Dec-2017.)

thm prodmo(setvar s0, setvar s1, setvar s2, setvar s3, setvar s4, setvar s5, setvar s6, class c0, class c1, class c2, class c3, wff w0) {
  |- wi(w0, wmo(s0, wo(wrex(s1, cz, w3a(wss(c0, cfv(cuz, cv(s1))), wrex(s2, cfv(cuz, cv(s1)), wex(s3, wa(wne(cv(s3), nat0), wbr(cseq(cv(s2), cmul, c1), cli, cv(s3))))), wbr(cseq(cv(s1), cmul, c1), cli, cv(s0)))), wrex(s1, cn, wex(s4, wa(wf1o(cv(s4), co(nat1, cfz, cv(s1)), c0), wceq(cv(s0), cfv(cseq(nat1, cmul, c2), cv(s1)))))))))
  -| wceq(c1, cmpt(s5, cz, cif(c3, nat1, wcel(cv(s5), c0))))
  -| wi(wa(w0, wcel(cv(s5), c0)), wcel(c3, cc))
  -| wceq(c2, cmpt(s6, cn, csb(s5, cfv(cv(s4), cv(s6)), c3)))
  -| diffss(s0, s1)
  -| diffss(s0, s2)
  -| diffss(s0, s3)
  -| diffss(s0, s4)

  -| diffss(s5, s6)
  -| diffsc(s0, c0)
